    gversioni2024.10.1ºfapp_idx io.github.bkueng.qMasterPassworddnameoqMasterPasswordgsummaryx!Stateless Master Password ManagerkscreenshotsüxYhttps://raw.githubusercontent.com/bkueng/qMasterPassword/main/screenshots/main_window.pngjcategoriespSecurity,Utilityprich_descriptiony╗qMasterPassword is a graphical password manager. Access all your passwords using only a single master password. But in contrast to other managers it does not store any passwords: Unique passwords are generated from the master password and a site name. This means you automatically get different passwords for each account and there is no password file that can be lost or get stolen. There is also no need to trust any online password service.gversione2.0.2¿fapp_idxio.github.bothlab.pomidaqdnamegPoMiDAQgsummaryx+View and record videos from UCLA Miniscopeseiconséxâhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/io/github/bothlab.pomidaq/7e02472e7fc840570df35bccb631fcf8/icons/128x128/io.github.bothlab.pomidaq.pngxàhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/io/github/bothlab.pomidaq/7e02472e7fc840570df35bccb631fcf8/icons/128x128@2/io.github.bothlab.pomidaq.pngkscreenshotséxthttps://dl.flathub.org/media/io/github/bothlab.pomidaq/7e02472e7fc840570df35bccb631fcf8/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngxthttps://dl.flathub.org/media/io/github/bothlab.pomidaq/7e02472e7fc840570df35bccb631fcf8/screenshots/image-2_orig.pngjcategoriesoScience,Biologyprich_descriptiony
      PoMiDAQ is a recording software for UCLA Miniscopes for neuroscientific research.
      It provides an easy way to record videos from Miniscopes, create Z-stacks to give an
      overview of visible cells or tissue features and provides an online background subtraction
      feature to gain an initial insight into cellular calcium activity while data is recorded.
      Recorded data is encoded with the FFV1 codec by default, to allow for smaller,
      lossless video files that are safe to archive.
