hydrus network client is a desktop application written for Anonymous and other internet enthusiasts with large media collections. It organises your files into an internal database and browses them with tags instead of folders, a little like a booru on your desktop. Tags and files can be anonymously shared through custom servers that any user may run. Everything is free, nothing phones home, and the source code is included with the release. It is developed mostly for Windows, but builds for Linux and macOS are available (perhaps with some limitations, depending on your situation).gversionc595¿fapp_iduio.github.hypengw.QcmdnamecQcmgsummaryxMaterial3 cloud music playereiconséx{https://dl.flathub.org/media/io/github/hypengw.Qcm/889ebccda52a386b22abf15e1d4d6be2/icons/128x128/io.github.hypengw.Qcm.pngx}https://dl.flathub.org/media/io/github/hypengw.Qcm/889ebccda52a386b22abf15e1d4d6be2/icons/128x128@2/io.github.hypengw.Qcm.pngkscreenshotséxphttps://dl.flathub.org/media/io/github/hypengw.Qcm/889ebccda52a386b22abf15e1d4d6be2/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngxphttps://dl.flathub.org/media/io/github/hypengw.Qcm/889ebccda52a386b22abf15e1d4d6be2/screenshots/image-2_orig.pngjcategorieseAudioprich_descriptionxMaterial3 cloud music playergversione1.1.2ºfapp_idx#io.github.iSlammedMyKindle.godotGemdnamehgodotGemgsummaryx>Controller client to emulate an xbox360 controller for windowskscreenshotsüxhttps://i.imgur.com/o1wmMeU.pngjcategoriesdGameprich_descriptionyäTurn your steam deck into a windows controller (Or use any controller from a Linux PC on windows). Connect linux to windows over the network in order to bind an emulated controller on windows to the same inputs you&apos;re doing on linux. Useful for playing games that might lack support for your controller out of the box, or just need another controller despite running out of USB portsgversione1.2.0¿fapp_idxio.github.idevecore.ValutadnamefValutagsummaryxConvert between currencieseiconséxàhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/io/github/