,Gameprich_descriptionyÏMuehle is a no frills implementation of the classical board game Nine Men&apos;s Morris. It does not have any cool features: no play against other humans (neither locally nor via the network), no play computer vs computer, no stats, no time control, no learning from play, no analysis mode, no variants for the rules of play. It&apos;s just to have some fun playing against the AI. The only additions: you can undo moves; and the AI will indicate when it thinks the position is dead even (you may take that as the AI offering a draw). You, on the other hand, cannot offer a draw: that would be pointless, as the AI is not designed to handle it anyway. Just quit or start a new game if you feel the current game is going nowhere.gversionpbison_2023-02-20¿fapp_idtnet.kuribo64.melonDSdnamegmelonDSgsummaryxNintendo DS and DSi emulatoreiconsüxyhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/net/kuribo64/melonDS/7746573288c90396cfdabbd67a4cecf9/icons/128x128/net.kuribo64.melonDS.pngkscreenshotsâxohttps://dl.flathub.org/media/net/kuribo64/melonDS/7746573288c90396cfdabbd67a4cecf9/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngxohttps://dl.flathub.org/media/net/kuribo64/melonDS/7746573288c90396cfdabbd67a4cecf9/screenshots/image-2_orig.pngxohttps://dl.flathub.org/media/net/kuribo64/melonDS/7746573288c90396cfdabbd67a4cecf9/screenshots/image-3_orig.pngjcategoriesmGame,Emulatorprich_descriptionxø
