5c00e3f99f7f43290d/icons/128x128/org.cloudcompare.CloudCompare.pngkscreenshotséxxhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/cloudcompare/CloudCompare/3ed341bbf9ee485c00e3f99f7f43290d/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngxxhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/cloudcompare/CloudCompare/3ed341bbf9ee485c00e3f99f7f43290d/screenshots/image-2_orig.pngjcategorieshGraphicsprich_descriptionylCloudCompare is a 3D point cloud (and triangular mesh) processing software. It has been originally designed to perform comparison between two dense 3D points clouds (such as the ones acquired with a laser scanner) or between a point cloud and a triangular mesh. It relies on a specific octree structure dedicated to this task.  Afterwards, it has been extended to a more generic point cloud processing software, including many advanced algorithms (registration, resampling, color/normal/scalar fields handling, statistics computation, sensor management, interactive or automatic segmentation, display enhancement, etc.).gversionf2.13.2¿fapp_idx!org.cockpit_project.CockpitClientdnamenCockpit Clientgsummaryx"Web-based server interface via ssheiconséxôhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/cockpit_project/CockpitClient/335079b1c8d670f5a2963cc76135bdd4/icons/128x128/org.cockpit_project.CockpitClient.pngxòhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/cockpit_project/CockpitClient/335079b1c8d670f5a2963cc76135bdd4/icons/128x128@2/org.cockpit_project.CockpitClient.pngkscreenshotsâx|https://dl.flathub.org/media/org/cockpit_project/CockpitClient/335079b1c8d670f5a2963cc76135bdd4/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngx|https://dl.flathub.org/media/org/cockpit_project/CockpitClient/335079b1c8d670f5a2963cc76135bdd4/screenshots/image-2_orig.pngx|https://dl.flathub.org/media/org/cockpit_project/CockpitClient/335079b1c8d670f5a2963cc76135bdd4/screenshots/image-3_orig.pngjcategoriestNetwork,RemoteAccessprich_descriptionx²
