		gversionf4.24.0¿fapp_idqorg.d3cod3.MosaicdnamefMosaicgsummaryx@An openFrameworks based Visual Patching Creative-Coding Platformeiconsüxshttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/d3cod3/Mosaic/c166c58ccc7885e252fa0b17ddc60e4a/icons/128x128/org.d3cod3.Mosaic.pngkscreenshotsàxlhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/d3cod3/Mosaic/c166c58ccc7885e252fa0b17ddc60e4a/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngxlhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/d3cod3/Mosaic/c166c58ccc7885e252fa0b17ddc60e4a/screenshots/image-2_orig.pngxlhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/d3cod3/Mosaic/c166c58ccc7885e252fa0b17ddc60e4a/screenshots/image-3_orig.pngxlhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/d3cod3/Mosaic/c166c58ccc7885e252fa0b17ddc60e4a/screenshots/image-4_orig.pngxlhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/d3cod3/Mosaic/c166c58ccc7885e252fa0b17ddc60e4a/screenshots/image-5_orig.pngjcategoriestGraphics,Developmentprich_descriptionyÜMosaic is a multi-platform livecoding programming/patching environment for creating real-time audio-visual compositions. It&apos;s principally designed for live needs, as can be teaching in class, live performing in an algorave, or running a generative audio-visual installation in a museum. It aims to empower artists, creative coders, scenographers and other creative technologists in their creative workflowgversione0.6.7¿fapp_idx#org.damask_multiphysics.DAMASK_griddnamekDAMASK gridgsummaryvGrid solver for DAMASKeiconséxùhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/damask_multiphysics/DAMASK_grid/756a5f45bd5ae8d65699a85247316765/icons/128x128/org.damask_multiphysics.DAMASK_grid.pngxÖhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/damask_multiphysics/DAMASK_grid/756a5f45bd5ae8d65699a85247316765/icons/128x128@2/org.damask_multiphysics.DAMASK_grid.pngkscreenshotséx~https://dl.flathub.org/media/org/damask_multiphysics/DAMASK_grid/756a5f45bd5ae8d65699a85247316765/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngx~https://dl.flathub.org/media/org/damask_multiphysics/DAMASK_grid/756a5f45bd5ae8d65699a85247316765/screenshots/image-2_orig.pngjcategoriessScience,Engineeringprich_descriptiony6
      DAMASK is a unified multi-physics crystal plasticity simulation package. The solution of continuum mechanical boundary value problems requires a constitutive response that connects deformation and stress at each material point. This problem is solved in DAMASK on the basis of crystal plasticity using a variety of constitutive models and homogenization approaches. However, treating mechanics in isolation is no longer sufficient to study emergent advanced high-strength materials. In these materials, deformation happens interrelated with displacive phase transformation, significant heating, and potential damage evolution. Therefore, DAMASK is capable of handling multi-physics problems. Following a modular approach, additional field equations are solved in a fully coupled way using a staggered approach.
    gversione3.0.1¿fapp_idx#org.damask_multiphysics.DAMASK_meshdnamekDAMASK meshgsummaryvMesh solver for DAMASKeiconséxùhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/damask_multiphysics/DAMASK_mesh/4261b2e166c2f239e2a1987f0aa6fd60/icons/128x128/org.damask_multiphysics.DAMASK_mesh.pngxÖhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/damask_multiphysics/DAMASK_mesh/4261b2e166c2f239e2a1987f0aa6fd60/icons/128x128@2/org.damask_multiphysics.DAMASK_mesh.pngkscreenshotséx~https://dl.flathub.org/media/org/damask_multiphysics/DAMASK_mesh/4261b2e166c2f239e2a1987f0aa6fd60/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngx~https://dl.flathub.org/media/org/damask_multiphysics/DAMASK_mesh/4261b2e166c2f239e2a1987f0aa6fd60/screenshots/image-2_orig.pngjcategoriessScience,Engineeringprich_descriptiony6
      DAMASK is a unified multi-physics crystal plasticity simulation package. The solution of continuum mechanical boundary value problems requires a constitutive response that connects deformation and stress at each material point. This problem is solved in DAMASK on the basis of crystal plasticity using a variety of constitutive models and homogenization approaches. However, treating mechanics in isolation is no longer sufficient to study emergent advanced high-strength materials. In these materials, deformation happens interrelated with displacive phase transformation, significant heating, and potential damage evolution. Therefore, DAMASK is capable of handling multi-physics problems. Following a modular approach, additional field equations are solved in a fully coupled way using a staggered approach.
