    eiconsüxhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/kde/kubrick.desktop/b18825d3a87f29a878d557832d1764e4/icons/128x128/org.kde.kubrick.desktop.pngkscreenshotsüxrhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/kde/kubrick.desktop/b18825d3a87f29a878d557832d1764e4/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngjcategoriesnGame,LogicGameprich_descriptionyÜ
      Kubrick is a game based on the Rubik&apos;s CubeÔäó puzzle. The cube sizes range
      from 2x2x2 up to 6x6x6, or you can play with irregular &quot;bricks&quot; such as 5x3x2
      or &quot;mats&quot; such as 6x4x1 or 2x2x1. The game has a selection of puzzles at
      several levels of difficulty, as well as demos of pretty patterns and
      solution moves, or you can make up your own puzzles.
