    gversionf1.19.1ºfapp_idxorg.libsdl.Maelstrom.desktopdnameiMaelstromgsummaryxHigh Quality Asteroids ClonekscreenshotsüxLhttps://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/44/Maelstrom_screenshot.pngjcategoriesoArcadeGame,Gameprich_descriptionxÓYou pilot your ship through the dreaded &quot;Maelstrom&quot; asteroid belt -- suddenly your best friend thrusts towards you and fires, directly at your cockpit. You raise your shields just in time, and the battle is joined.gversione3.0.7¿fapp_idtorg.libvips.vipsdispdnamehVipsdispgsummarylImage viewereiconsüxyhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/libvips/vipsdisp/1a35339ce6c5762290c8e123ca28fc5a/icons/128x128/org.libvips.vipsdisp.pngkscreenshotsäxohttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/libvips/vipsdisp/1a35339ce6c5762290c8e123ca28fc5a/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngxohttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/libvips/vipsdisp/1a35339ce6c5762290c8e123ca28fc5a/screenshots/image-2_orig.pngxohttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/libvips/vipsdisp/1a35339ce6c5762290c8e123ca28fc5a/screenshots/image-3_orig.pngxohttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/libvips/vipsdisp/1a35339ce6c5762290c8e123ca28fc5a/screenshots/image-4_orig.pngjcategoriesx"Graphics,2DGraphics,RasterGraphicsprich_descriptiony
Vipsdisp can display huge (many, many gigabyte) images quickly and without
using much memory.

As well as the usual PNG, JPG, TIF, PDF, SVG, WEBP, JP2, JXL and GIF,
it supports many scientific and technical image formats, including SVS,
MRXS, OpenEXR, FITS, Matlab, NIfTI, Analyze, and PFM.

Vipsdisp supports pixel types from 1 bit mono to 128-bit double precision
complex, you can convert image formats, it support copy-paste and drag-drop,
and it has a range of useful visualisation tools and display modes.
