  gversionf0.48.0¿fapp_idxorg.opennumismat.OpenNumismatdnamelOpenNumismatgsummaryxCustom coin collection catalogeiconséxïhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/opennumismat/OpenNumismat/62f5fcd593c18271bdc391ebe330be47/icons/128x128/org.opennumismat.OpenNumismat.pngxìhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/opennumismat/OpenNumismat/62f5fcd593c18271bdc391ebe330be47/icons/128x128@2/org.opennumismat.OpenNumismat.pngkscreenshotsâxxhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/opennumismat/OpenNumismat/62f5fcd593c18271bdc391ebe330be47/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngxxhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/opennumismat/OpenNumismat/62f5fcd593c18271bdc391ebe330be47/screenshots/image-2_orig.pngxxhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/opennumismat/OpenNumismat/62f5fcd593c18271bdc391ebe330be47/screenshots/image-3_orig.pngjcategoriesgUtilityprich_descriptionxÅOpenNumismat is a handy and reliable application aimed at coin collectors, numismatists or amateurs looking to create a numismatics collection.gversionf1.9.12¿fapp_idsorg.openrgb.OpenRGBdnamegOpenRGBgsummaryx Open source RGB lighting controleiconsüxwhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/openrgb/OpenRGB/de36c468b6d851bbd868be4987220c7b/icons/128x128/org.openrgb.OpenRGB.pngkscreenshotsüxnhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/openrgb/OpenRGB/de36c468b6d851bbd868be4987220c7b/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngjcategoriesgUtilityprich_descriptionyÅ
      One of the biggest complaints about RGB is the software ecosystem
      surrounding it.  Every manufacturer has their own app, their own brand,
      their own style.  If you want to mix and match devices, you end up with a
      ton of conflicting, functionally identical apps competing for your
      background resources.  On top of that, these apps are proprietary and
      Windows-only.  Some even require online accounts.  What if there was a way
      to control all of your RGB devices from a single app, on both Windows and
      Linux, without any nonsense?  That is what OpenRGB sets out to achieve.
      One app to rule them all.
