      Password Safe is a password manager. It stores your passwords in an encrypted file, allowing you to remember only one password (the &quot;master password&quot;), instead of all the username/password combinations that you use. For extra security, you can use a Yubikey device to provide two-factor authentication.
    gversiongv1.20.0¿fapp_idxorg.pydpainter.PyDPainterdnamejPyDPaintergsummarywPixel art paint programeiconséxâhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/pydpainter/PyDPainter/9f207a658279f59e6e09f2e7bf764b45/icons/128x128/org.pydpainter.PyDPainter.pngxàhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/pydpainter/PyDPainter/9f207a658279f59e6e09f2e7bf764b45/icons/128x128@2/org.pydpainter.PyDPainter.pngkscreenshotsüxthttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/pydpainter/PyDPainter/9f207a658279f59e6e09f2e7bf764b45/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngjcategoriessGraphics,2DGraphicsprich_descriptionymPyDPainter, pronounced &quot;Pied Painter&quot; (like Pied Piper), is an attempt to create a usable pixel art program in Python using PyGame. The original inspiration came from the Commodore Amiga version of Deluxe Paint released by Electronic Arts in 1985. Back then, Deluxe Paint helped define the user interface of a paint program with tool bars, menus, and the novel use of left and right mouse buttons for painting and erasing. After pixel art gave way to photo-realism and high-resolution 24 bit color, Deluxe Paint was largely forgotten for artistic work -- left behind in the ever-progressing march of technology.gversione2.0.1¿fapp_idoorg.pymol.PyMOLdnamexPython Molecular Graphicsgsummaryx&Molecular visualization and raytracingeiconséxohttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/pymol/PyMOL/9b08e12478f219f2c15caddec187f872/icons/128x128/org.pymol.PyMOL.pngxqhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/pymol/PyMOL/9b08e12478f219f2c15caddec187f872/icons/128x128@2/org.pymol.PyMOL.pngkscreenshotsâxjhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/pymol/PyMOL/9b08e12478f219f2c15caddec187f872/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngxjhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/pymol/PyMOL/9b08e12478f219f2c15caddec187f872/screenshots/image-2_orig.pngxjhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/pymol/PyMOL/9b08e12478f219f2c15caddec187f872/screenshots/image-3_orig.pngjcategoriesqScience,Chemistryprich_descriptionx³
