    gversione1.2.5¿fapp_idtorg.swi_prolog.swipldnamejSWI-Prologgsummaryx&ISO/Edinburgh-style Prolog interpretereiconsüxyhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/swi_prolog/swipl/d893f383ab2f41d9d302211e735d2c92/icons/128x128/org.swi_prolog.swipl.pngkscreenshotsüxohttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/swi_prolog/swipl/d893f383ab2f41d9d302211e735d2c92/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngjcategorieskDevelopmentprich_descriptiony█
      SWI-Prolog is an open source (BSD-2) implementation of the Prolog language with many extensions. It is implemented in C (version 11) and Prolog and is available for many platforms (Linux, practically any POSIX like system, MacOS, Windows). All CPUs supported by Debian Linux are supported. A prototype running in your browser based on WASM (Web Assembly) is available. 
      (SWI-)Prolog is a versatile language. It is being used for business rule validation, natural language processing, software verification, software refactoring, network configuration, security, robotics, reasoning in legal and medical domains, graph processing, machine learning (ILP, PLP), linked data (RDF), mathematical proofs, and much more.
    gversionf9.3.15¿fapp_idworg.synfig.SynfigStudiodnamemSynfig Studiogsummaryx.Create and edit 2D animations and compositionseiconséxhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/synfig/SynfigStudio/04b93a93fa24d0ecfdb489070af5bcfa/icons/128x128/org.synfig.SynfigStudio.pngxühttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/synfig/SynfigStudio/04b93a93fa24d0ecfdb489070af5bcfa/icons/128x128@2/org.synfig.SynfigStudio.pngkscreenshotsàxrhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/synfig/SynfigStudio/04b93a93fa24d0ecfdb489070af5bcfa/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngxrhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/synfig/SynfigStudio/04b93a93fa24d0ecfdb489070af5bcfa/screenshots/image-2_orig.pngxrhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/synfig/SynfigStudio/04b93a93fa24d0ecfdb489070af5bcfa/screenshots/image-3_orig.pngxrhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/synfig/SynfigStudio/04b93a93fa24d0ecfdb489070af5bcfa/screenshots/image-4_orig.pngxrhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/synfig/SynfigStudio/04b93a93fa24d0ecfdb489070af5bcfa/screenshots/image-5_orig.pngjcategoriesx"Graphics,2DGraphics,VectorGraphicsprich_descriptionyLSynfig Studio is a free and open-source 2D animation software, designed as powerful industrial-strength solution for creating film-quality animation using a vector and bitmap artwork. It eliminates the need to create animation frame-by frame, allowing you to produce 2D animation of a higher quality with fewer people and resources.gversione1.5.3¿fapp_iduorg.syntalos.syntalosdnamehSyntalosgsummaryxRSynchronized data acquisition from diverse sources and flexible experiment controleiconséx{https://dl.flathub.org/media/org/syntalos/syntalos/c3e3afd56a49f505835698979e46d8fc/icons/128x128/org.syntalos.syntalos.pngx}https://dl.flathub.org/media/org/syntalos/syntalos/c3e3afd56a49f505835698979e46d8fc/icons/128x128@2/org.syntalos.syntalos.pngkscreenshotsâxphttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/syntalos/syntalos/c3e3afd56a49f505835698979e46d8fc/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngxphttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/syntalos/syntalos/c3e3afd56a49f505835698979e46d8fc/screenshots/image-2_orig.pngxphttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/syntalos/syntalos/c3e3afd56a49f505835698979e46d8fc/screenshots/image-3_orig.pngjcategoriesoScience,Biologyprich_descriptionyó
      Syntalos is a software for timestamp-synchronized parallel data acquisition from diverse data sources,
      such as cameras, microendoscopes, Intan electrophysiology amplifiers or Firmata-based serial interfaces.
      The software also allows closed-loop interventions via its built-in Python scripting support.
      It is specifically designed for use in (neuro)scientific in vivo behavior experiments.
