    gversionfv0.6.7ºfapp_idqorg.tomviz.TomvizdnamefTomvizgsummaryxEFree and open source tomographic visualization of nanoscale materialskscreenshotsëxAhttps://tomviz.readthedocs.io/en/latest/img/tomviz_screenshot.pngxIhttps://tomviz.readthedocs.io/en/latest/img/tomviz_start_end_pipeline.pngx<https://tomviz.readthedocs.io/en/latest/img/default_view.pngx@https://tomviz.readthedocs.io/en/latest/img/contour_color_by.pngx7https://tomviz.readthedocs.io/en/latest/img/outline.pngxChttps://tomviz.readthedocs.io/en/latest/img/inverted_clip_plane.pngxLhttps://tomviz.readthedocs.io/en/latest/img/brightness_and_contrast_auto.pngx@https://tomviz.readthedocs.io/en/latest/img/tilt_axis_dialog.pngx?https://tomviz.readthedocs.io/en/latest/img/tilt_axis_color.pngjcategoriesqChemistry,Scienceprich_descriptionyµTomviz is an open source software platform for reproducible volumetric visualization and data processing. The platform is designed for a wide range scientific applications but is especially tailored to high-resolution electron tomography, with features that allow alignment and reconstruction of nanoscale materials. The tomviz platform allows graphical analysis of 3D datasets, but also comes packaged with Python, NumPy, and SciPy tools to allow advanced data processing and analysis.gversionf1.10.0¿fapp_idxorg.tordini.flavio.MinitubednamehMinitubegsummarykYouTube appncontent_ratingy┘
