    gversione1.2.1ªfapp_idoorg.winehq.WinednamedWinegsummaryx<Run Windows applications on Linux, BSD, Solaris and Mac OS Xkscreenshotsäx>https://dl.winehq.org/share/images/screenshots/outlook2010.jpgx8https://dl.winehq.org/share/images/screenshots/steam.jpgx<https://dl.winehq.org/share/images/screenshots/goggalaxy.jpgxChttps://dl.winehq.org/share/images/screenshots/skyrim_specialed.jpgprich_descriptiony÷Wine (originally an acronym for &quot;Wine Is Not an Emulator&quot;) is a compatibility layer capable of running Windows applications on several POSIX-compliant operating systems, such as Linux, Mac OSX, &amp; BSD. Instead of simulating internal Windows logic like a virtual machine or emulator, Wine translates Windows API calls into POSIX calls on-the-fly, eliminating the performance and memory penalties of other methods and allowing you to cleanly integrate Windows applications into your desktop.gversionc7.0ªfapp_idoorg.winehq.WinednamedWinegsummaryx<Run Windows applications on Linux, BSD, Solaris and Mac OS Xkscreenshotsäx>https://dl.winehq.org/share/images/screenshots/outlook2010.jpgx8https://dl.winehq.org/share/images/screenshots/steam.jpgx<https://dl.winehq.org/share/images/screenshots/goggalaxy.jpgxChttps://dl.winehq.org/share/images/screenshots/skyrim_specialed.jpgprich_descriptiony÷Wine (originally an acronym for &quot;Wine Is Not an Emulator&quot;) is a compatibility layer capable of running Windows applications on several POSIX-compliant operating systems, such as Linux, Mac OSX, &amp; BSD. Instead of simulating internal Windows logic like a virtual machine or emulator, Wine translates Windows API calls into POSIX calls on-the-fly, eliminating the performance and memory penalties of other methods and allowing you to cleanly integrate Windows applications into your desktop.gversione8.0.2ªfapp_idoorg.winehq.WinednamedWinegsummaryxWindows compatibility layerkscreenshotsäxjhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/winehq/Wine/a20e03d8c95525cac3f4c27c9c2a6cb6/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngxjhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/winehq/Wine/a20e03d8c95525cac3f4c27c9c2a6cb6/screenshots/image-2_orig.pngxjhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/winehq/Wine/a20e03d8c95525cac3f4c27c9c2a6cb6/screenshots/image-3_orig.pngxjhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/winehq/Wine/a20e03d8c95525cac3f4c27c9c2a6cb6/screenshots/image-4_orig.pngprich_descriptiony&
      Wine (originally an acronym for &quot;Wine Is Not an Emulator&quot;) is a compatibility
      layer capable of running Windows applications on several POSIX-compliant
      operating systems, such as Linux, Mac OSX, &amp; BSD. Instead of simulating
      internal Windows logic like a virtual machine or emulator, Wine translates
      Windows API calls into POSIX calls on-the-fly, eliminating the performance
      and memory penalties of other methods and allowing you to cleanly integrate
      Windows applications into your desktop.
    gversionc9.0ªfapp_idoorg.winehq.WinednamedWinegsummaryxWindows compatibility layerkscreenshotsäxjhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/winehq/Wine/a20e03d8c95525cac3f4c27c9c2a6cb6/screenshots/image-1_orig.pngxjhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/winehq/Wine/a20e03d8c95525cac3f4c27c9c2a6cb6/screenshots/image-2_orig.pngxjhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/winehq/Wine/a20e03d8c95525cac3f4c27c9c2a6cb6/screenshots/image-3_orig.pngxjhttps://dl.flathub.org/media/org/winehq/Wine/a20e03d8c95525cac3f4c27c9c2a6cb6/screenshots/image-4_orig.pngprich_descriptiony&
      Wine (originally an acronym for &quot;Wine Is Not an Emulator&quot;) is a compatibility
      layer capable of running Windows applications on several POSIX-compliant
      operating systems, such as Linux, Mac OSX, &amp; BSD. Instead of simulating
      internal Windows logic like a virtual machine or emulator, Wine translates
      Windows API calls into POSIX calls on-the-fly, eliminating the performance
      and memory penalties of other methods and allowing you to cleanly integrate
      Windows applications into your desktop.
