      The Freedesktop Platform is a basic runtime for flatpak application
      that contains the most basic libraries and files needed to run
      a linux desktop application. It contains selection of software that
      form a stable ABI for building Flatpak applications including but
      not limited to latest versions of the freedesktop technologies like
      X11, Mesa, Wayland, dbus, cairo, gstreamer. It also contains
      SDL2.
